HEADWORD: Hexicology
<hw>Hex`i*col"ogy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ state
or habit + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <def>The science which treats of the
complex relations of living creatures to other organisms, and to their
surrounding conditions generally.</def> <-- = ecology --> <rj><au>St.
George Mivart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

